   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:lang="grc"
              subtype="transcription"
              xml:id="tibe0006.transcription"
              corresp="#tibe0006.translation">
            <p>Μνησθῇ εἰς ἀγαθὸν καὶ εἰς <lb/>
                    εὐλογίαν Προφοτοῦρος ὁ μιζό<lb break="no"/>τερος ἐποίησεν τὴν στοὰν ταύ<lb break="no"/>την τοῦ ἁγίου τόπου. Ἐυλογία αὐτῷ <lb/>
                    Ἀμήν. <foreign xml:lang="heb">שלום</foreign>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="tibe0006.translation"
              corresp="#tibe0006.transcription">
            <p>May he be remembered for good and for blessing. Profoturos the elder constructed this aisle of the synagogue. Blessing upon him. Amen. Shalom</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
            <p>A rectangle frame composed of two rows of black tesserae surrounds this inscription,
          which was apparently inserted sometime after the mosaic's initial construction by cutting
          out an area of the floor. Ivy leaves of red tesserae flank line 5. The letters resemble
          third century paleography at Gerasa and fourth century forms from Antioch, and seem to
          have been executed by someone familiar with the Greek. </p>
         </div>
